{
  "texts": [
    "We construct sentence similarity dataset covering 26 languages by utilizing the translation samples from two machine translation datasets, i.e., MAFAND (Adelani et al., 2022a) and NusaX-MT (Winata et al., 2022b).",
    "We create a balanced dataset with 50% positive pairs and 50% negative pairs over all 26 languages.",
    "We measure the cross-lingual semantic similarity performance of using Sentence Transformers (Reimers and Gurevych, 2019).",
    "We also conduct monolingual semantic similarity analysis for various languages using the data from SemEval 2024 Task 12: Textual Semantic Relatedness dataset foot_2.",
    "For the monolingual semantic similarity we add additional word frequency features including bag-of-words and TF-IDF to improve the retrieval quality of the semantic similarity model."
  ]
}